<DATE_TIME> 2000-08-29 00:19 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Seattle Releases QB Foley  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
   KIRKLAND, Wash. (AP) -- Veteran quarterback Glenn Foley was
released Monday by the Seattle Seahawks in a cost-cutting move.
</P>
<P>
   Foley, the team's backup quarterback last season, started one
game in 1999 when Jon Kitna was injured. He lost his backup job to
second-year player Brock Huard, who performed better during the
preseason.
</P>
<P>
   The $500,000-plus Foley was to receive this season played into
the decision, said coach and general manager Mike Holmgren.
</P>
<P>
   ''The salary cap factors into it,'' Holmgren said. ''Having a
veteran as your third (quarterback), there's a certain comfort
level there, but we're about training young people right now.''
</P>
<P>
   Matt Lytle, one of four players signed by the Seahawks on
Monday, will be the No. 3 quarterback this season. He spent last
season with Carolina, but was released by the Panthers on Sunday.
</P>
<P>
   Seattle cut Todd Peterson, the second-leading field goal kicker
in team history, on Sunday in another salary-related move.
</P>
<P>
   ''When it comes to kickers or punters that are good players, and
Todd's a good player, there's usually more than one reason you do
that,'' Holmgren said. ''It was a combination of playing outside
and the cap situation.''
</P>
<P>
   The Seahawks will play at University of Washington's Husky
Stadium this season after the implosion of the Kingdome.
</P>
<P>
   Peterson, who stopped by the team's practice facility Monday,
said he has been contacted by two other teams.
</P>
<P>
   ''It's not for me to second-guess,'' Peterson said. ''It's for
me to move on and get ready to roll. I'm going to talk to teams,
figure out what's the best opportunity, then I'm going to go kick
somewhere.''
</P>
<P>
   Kris Heppner, a rookie free agent from Montana, will be the
Seahawks' kicker this season.
</P>
<P>
Notes: In addition to Lytle, the Seahawks signed three other
players from the waiver wire: defensive end Rahmaan Streeter, guard
Eric King and fullback Scot Osborne. They also waived offensive
lineman Jeff Dellenbach.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
