<HEADLINE> Stock Slip in Early Trading  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
   NEW YORK (AP) -- Stock prices are mostly lower in early trading.
The Dow Jones industrial average is down 28 points in today's early
going. Losing issues on the New York Stock Exchange hold a 7-5 lead
over gainers.
</P>
<P>
   The Nasdaq Composite Index is down one point and the Standard &AMP;
Poor's 500 Stock Index is down three points.
</P>
<P>
   The market has a couple of modest negatives hanging over it in
the news department. AT&AMP;T warned that third quarter earnings will
be lower than expected because of a faster consolidation of Excite
At Home results. On the technology side, Intel has stopped
shipments of its fastest chip because of a flaw.
</P>
<P>
   The market will get a double-dose of economic news in the coming
minutes. That will be consumer confidence from the Conference
Board, and new home sales for July.
</P>
</TEXT>
