<HEADLINE> Business news in brief from around New Jersey  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	   JERSEY CITY, N.J. (AP) - Provident Savings Bank and Ridgewood
Savings Bank have agreed to merge, the two companies announced
Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
   Under the agreement, Ridgewood Savings Bank will operate as a
division of Provident Savings Bank. Stockholders of Ridgewood
Financial Inc. will receive $15 in cash for each share of common
stock. The estimated stock value is $22 million.
</P>
<P>
   Provident Savings Bank is a mutual state savings bank
headquartered in Jersey City with 51 branches.
</P>
<P>
   Ridgewood Savings Bank is a subsidiary of Ridgewood Financial
Inc. and operates four branches in Ridgewood and Mahwah.
</P>
<P>
   ISELIN, N.J. (AP) - Pharmos Corp. has agreed to provide the
licensing of two drug formulas to Senju Pharmaceutical Co., Ltd. of
Japan.
</P>
<P>
   Under the agreement announced Tuesday, Senju can develop and
market two similar drugs called Lotemax and Alrex in the United
States.
</P>
<P>
   Lotemax is an ophthalmic anti-inflammatory drug, and Alrex is an
anti-allergy drug.
</P>
<P>
   The Iselin-based biopharmaceutical company develops drugs for
the central nervous system and ophthalmic ailments.
</P>
<P>
   MADISON, N.J. (AP) - Wyeth-Ayerst Laboratories has received
approval to market the pill form of Rapamune, a transplant
immunosuppressant, the pharmaceutical company announced Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
   The U.S. Food and Drug Administration approved the 1 mg tablet,
which is used to prevent organ rejection in kidney transplant
patients.
</P>
<P>
   The company was already marketing the liquid form of Rapamune.
</P>
<P>
   Wyeth-Ayerst Laboratories is a division of American Home
Products Corp.
</P>
<P>
   YARDVILLE, N.J. (AP) - Martin Tuchman has been named to
Yardville National Bancorp Inc.'s Board of Directors, the bank
company announced Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
   Tuchman is chairman and chief executive officer of Interpool,
Inc., a Princeton-based chassis leasing company. Interpool is
listed on the New York Stock Exchange.
</P>
<P>
   Yardville National Bancorp operates 12 Yardville National Bank
branches in Mercer County.
</P>
<P>
   NEWARK, N.J. (AP) - Mutual fund customers with Prudential
Insurance Co. can now make transactions through its Web site.
</P>
<P>
   Through www.prudential.com, customers can access their mutual
fund accounts and transfer shares from one fund to another, and
review 18 months of transaction history and details of investment
plans.
</P>
<P>
   Customers can already get current values and other information
about their life insurance, property and casualty policies.
</P>
<P>
   The insurance company is headquartered in Newark.
</P>
<P>
   PRINCETON, N.J. (AP) - RCN Corp. will soon offer cable,
telephone and Internet services to San Francisco residents, the
company announced Monday.
</P>
<P>
   The company expects to sign up customers by the end of the year.
</P>
<P>
   RCN offers services through its fiber-optic network in northern
New Jersey, New York City and Philadelphia.
</P>
<P>
   GREENWICH, Conn. (AP) - Northern and central New Jersey
residents can choose to receive electricity from The New Power Co.,
a residential and small business energy provider.
</P>
<P>
   The Connecticut-based company said customers will save money,
and receive frequent filer miles from Continental, American, US
Airways and Delta airlines, and other incentives.
</P>
<P>
   New Jersey customers receive power from PSE&AMP;G.
</P>
</TEXT>
