<BODY>
<HEADLINE> NYPA to buy up to 11 gas turbine generator sets  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	   ALBANY, N.Y. (AP) - Citing the need to ensure adequate power
supply for next summer, the New York Power Authority trustees
Tuesday authorized the purchase of up to 11 gas turbine generator
sets.
</P>
<P>
   NYPA officials said it will cost as much as $220 million to buy
up to 520 megawatts of electric generating capacity.
</P>
<P>
   While plans to build new power plants in the state are being
discussed, officials said the earliest that any such project could
be completed would be in the summer of 2002. NYPA said the new
generators would help meet any potential shortfalls, or
''generation gap,'' by being in place by next summer.
</P>
<P>
   Power Authority Chairman Clarence Rappleyea said it was
necessary to purchase the generating units immediately because of
global competition for the equipment. If NYPA doesn't act now,
Rappleyea said the units would ''most likely be unavailable when
needed.''
</P>
<P>
   Rappleyea said NYPA is looking for the best sites for the
generators, he said.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
