<DATE_TIME> 2000-08-29 20:30 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Carter: No Deal With Nike  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
   LAHAINA, Hawaii (AP) -- Vince Carter denied an Internet report
Tuesday that he has reached agreement with Nike on a 6-year, $30
million endorsement contract.
</P>
<P>
   ''There's no deal. Everybody thinks they know everything that's
going on with me. I'm tired of it, really,'' Carter said at the
U.S. Olympic basketball team training camp. ''I just got out of a
Puma suit, so how can I have a deal ready?
</P>
<P>
   ''Everybody's jumping the gun.''
</P>
<P>
   The Toronto Raptors forward broke his contract with Puma last
season, and an arbitrator recently ruled that Carter owes the
company $13.5 million, plus $1 million in attorneys fees.
</P>
<P>
   The Web site HoopsTV.com reported that Carter's deal with Nike
was agreed to, but an attorney for Puma also disputed that.
</P>
<P>
   ''There isn't anything pending,'' the lawyer, Norman Oberstein,
said. ''We're just trying to work things out, and hopefully we
will.''
</P>
</TEXT>
