<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Forego Ready for Saratoga  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
   SARATOGA SPRINGS, N.Y. (AP) -- Richter Scale will carry the high
weight among 10 contenders in the 21st running of the $250,000
Forego Handicap at Saratoga Race Course on Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
   Richard Kaster's 6-year-old will concede from 4-11 pounds to his
rivals in the Forego, which has been shortened to 6&AMP;frac12; furlongs this
year.
</P>
<P>
   Since trainer Mary Jo Lohmeier returned Richter Scale from the
turf to the dirt, he has recorded five wins in six starts. With
career earnings of $1.1 million, the veteran campaigner is a
serious contender for divisional honors.
</P>
<P>
   ''He's just having a very good year,'' Lohmeier said. ''He's
always had a history of foot problems, so we tried him on the turf
last year. It turned out that he only liked the turf if it was rock
hard. He's been on the dirt ever since.''
</P>
<P>
   Intidab and Successful Appeal, the first two finishers in
Saratoga's A.G. Vanderbilt Handicap, will be on hand to provide
competition.
</P>
<P>
   Successful Appeal was declared the winner of the A.G. Vanderbilt
after Intidab, the first finisher, was deemed to have interfered
with him in the stretch run.
</P>
<P>
   Intidab was seventh in last year's Forego. Trainer Kiaran
McLaughlin is expecting a much better performance from him this
time. Meet-leading rider Jerry Bailey enhances his prospects.
</P>
<P>
   Trainer John Kimmel is confident that his charge, Successful
Appeal, will also run well in the Forego.
</P>
<P>
   ''He breezed last Wednesday and has been training very well.
He's more mature, bigger, and has more flesh than he did as a
3-year-old. Hopefully, there won't be any bumping incidents this
time. It's going to be a good race.''
</P>
<P>
   From the rail out the Forego field is: Proven Cure, 112, Shane
Sellers; Intidab, 118, Jerry Bailey; Iron Punch, 115, Carlos Cruz;
Bright Valour, 113, Pat Day; One Way Love, 116, Patrick Husbands;
Silver Season, 115, Eibar Coa; Successful Appeal, 119, Edgar Prado;
Chasin' Wimmin, 112, Jean-Luc Samyn; Shadow Caster, 113, Jorge
Chavez and Richter Scale, 121, Richard Migliore.
</P>
</TEXT>
