<HEADLINE> Ramirez Placed on DL  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
   PITTSBURGH (AP) -- Pittsburgh Pirates third baseman Aramis
Ramirez, who probably miss the rest of the season, was placed on
the 15-day disabled list Tuesday because of a separated left
shoulder.
</P>
<P>
   Ramirez was injured diving for a ball in the first inning Monday
night. His roster spot was taken by infielder Abraham Nunez, who
was recalled from Triple-A Nashville.
</P>
<P>
   Manager Gene Lamont said most of the playing time at third base
will go to Enrique Wilson, acquired from Cleveland on July 29.
</P>
<P>
   Ramirez opened the season with the Pirates but was sent to
Nashville on April 28 with a .167 average.
</P>
<P>
   Since returning, he increased his average to .256 and was
hitting .327 in his last 27 games with four homers and 21 RBIs.
</P>
<P>
   Lamont said there is a slight possibility Ramirez might be able
to play before the season ends on Oct. 1.
</P>
</TEXT>
