<HEADLINE> Tree service employee dies from 80-foot fall  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	   NORTH GREENBUSH, N.Y. (AP) - A 33-year-old tree service worker
fell 80-feet to his death Tuesday morning.
</P>
<P>
   Peter Donzelli of nearby Troy was pronounced dead at the scene.
</P>
<P>
   Police say Donzelli, an employee with Paradise Tree Service of
Troy, was working on a towering pine tree when a branch broke,
apparently weakened from a lightning strike. The branch landed on
top of Donzelli, crushing him.
</P>
<P>
   An investigation by police and the Occupational Safety and
Health administration is continuing.
</P>
</TEXT>
