<HEADLINE> Lights Go Out at Reds-Braves Game  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
   ATLANTA (AP) -- The lights at Turner Field flickered and then
went out as the Atlanta Braves came to bat in the bottom of the
ninth inning against the Cincinnati Reds.
</P>
<P>
   With the Braves trailing 4-2, Andres Galarraga stepped in to bat
against Cincinnati closer Danny Graves. Before the first pitch, the
lights went out momentarily, causing the crowd to groan and
Galarraga to step out of the box.
</P>
<P>
   A few seconds later, all of the lights atop Turner Field went
out, except for a section along the first-base line. The scoreboard
and most of the other power within the stadium was functioning, but
the field was mostly dark.
</P>
<P>
   Team officials described the outage as a ''power spike'' and
quickly took care of the problem. The lights came back on and play
resumed after a 12-minute delay.
</P>
<P>
   During the outage, the crowd was entertained with songs like
''The Night The Lights Went Out In Georgia'' and ''Dancing In The
Dark.''
</P>
</TEXT>
