<HEADLINE> Ariz. Crash Kills 3 Immigrants  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
   TUCSON, Ariz. (AP) -- A van carrying illegal immigrants crashed
Tuesday on Interstate 10 following a blowout, killing three people
and injuring 17.
</P>
<P>
   The driver apparently fled, according to the Department of
Public Safety.
</P>
<P>
   The van's right rear tire blew, causing the vehicle to roll into
the median and eject two men and a woman, said DPS Sgt. Ed Slechta
said. The three ejected died.
</P>
<P>
   Slechta said the van had no seats other than for the driver and
front passenger, which he said was typical of a vehicle set up to
smuggle immigrants.
</P>
